---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
<section class="hero">
  <h1>Building scalable systems,<br>one component at a time.</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Frontend Architect | Advocate for Module Federation & Rspack Ecosystem | Micro Frontends & Tooling</p>
  <p class="description">
  I write about software architecture, microfrontends, and system design. 
  Sharing insights from building distributed systems and modern web applications.
  </p>
  <div class="cta-buttons">
    <a href="/blog" class="btn btn-primary">Read My Writing</a>
    <a href="https://github.com/YanPes" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View GitHub</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Recent Articles</h2>
  <div class="blog-preview">
    <article class="article-card">
      <div class="article-meta">January 2026 · 8 min read</div>
      <h3>Module Federation in Practice: Lessons from Production</h3>
      <p class="article-excerpt">
        After implementing module federation across multiple teams, I've learned what works 
        and what doesn't. Here are the patterns that emerged from real-world usage.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="article-card">
      <div class="article-meta">December 2025 · 12 min read</div>
      <h3>The State of Microfrontends: Architecture Patterns That Scale</h3>
      <p class="article-excerpt">
        A deep dive into microfrontend architectures, comparing build-time integration, 
        runtime composition, and edge-side includes for different use cases.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="article-card">
      <div class="article-meta">November 2025 · 6 min read</div>
      <h3>System Design Principles: Composability Over Complexity</h3>
      <p class="article-excerpt">
        Why breaking systems into composable pieces leads to more maintainable architectures, 
        and how to identify the right boundaries.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>About Me</h2>
  <div class="about-grid">
    <p class="bio">
      I'm a software engineer focused on building scalable web applications and distributed systems. 
      My work centers on frontend architecture, microfrontends, and creating maintainable codebases 
      that teams can evolve over time. I believe in sharing knowledge and learning in public.
    </p>

    <div class="stats-grid">
      <div class="stat-item">
        <div class="stat-label">Focus Areas</div>
        <div class="stat-value">Architecture, Microfrontends</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-item">
        <div class="stat-label">Location</div>
        <div class="stat-value">Schwäbisch Gmünd, DE</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-item">
        <div class="stat-label">Currently</div>
        <div class="stat-value">Building & Writing</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>

<style>
.hero {
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  padding: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
}

.hero .subtitle {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.25rem);
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  font-weight: 300;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
}

.hero .description {
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  max-width: 600px;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
}

.cta-buttons {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--spacing-sm);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
}

.btn {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 400;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}

.btn-primary {
  background-color: var(--accent);
  color: var(--bg-primary);
  border-color: var(--accent);
}

.btn-primary:hover {
  background-color: var(--accent-hover);
  border-color: var(--accent-hover);
}

.btn-secondary {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--text-primary);
}

.btn-secondary:hover {
  background-color: var(--bg-secondary);
}


.blog-preview {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--spacing-lg);
}

.article-card {
  text-decoration: none;
  color: inherit;
  display: block;
  padding-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}

.article-card:last-child {
  border-bottom: none;
}

.article-meta {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: 14px;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.article-card h3 {
  transition: color 0.2s ease;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
}

.article-card:hover h3 {
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}

.article-excerpt {
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.about-grid {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--spacing-lg);
}

.bio {
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  line-height: 1.7;
}

.stats-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
  gap: var(--spacing-md);
  margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
}

.stat-item {
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  background-color: var(--bg-secondary);
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}

.stat-label {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
}

.stat-value {
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--text-primary);
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
  .article-card {
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .article-card:hover {
    transform: translateX(4px);
  }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .hero {
    padding: var(--spacing-md) 0;
  }

  .cta-buttons {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .btn {
    flex: 1;
    text-align: center;
    min-width: 140px;
  }
}
</style>
